content.description:
Climb the short, techy face behind a tree.  This route is characterized by uninspiring, crumbly rock.  Listed in the Perkins guide as 5.12a, I could not find a suitable sequence that went at anywhere near that grade.  There are much better routes of a similar style in the area if that's what you're looking for (go get on

Tower of Power

).

content.location:
This climb is located in the narrow corridor between Bulldog Balcony and lower Bulldog Wall.  Approach as for Lower Bulldog and hike around on looker's left and uphill through a steep, loose gully.  There are 3 climbs on this section of Bulldog Balcony; Petey is the second and shares the first bolt with the route to the left (

Roberto's

).
